The paper discusses the use of Evolution Strategies (ESs) for training deep neural networks in reinforcement learning tasks, which are a form of controller design. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with optimization problems in high-dimensional spaces, which suggests that it may also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. The paper also discusses control problems, which suggests that it may belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the handling of uncertainty in stochastic fitness functions, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
